        <content><![CDATA[    <h1 class="title topictitle1">Create HR Bulk Cases</h1>        <div class="body taskbody">        <div class="li step p">                <span class="ph cmd">Complete or edit the form.</span>                <table class="simpletable choicetable choicetableborder" id="sn_hr_core_hr_generate_mass_cases-normal__choicetable_mcj_cpn_2bb"><thead><tr><th id="d486748e29-option">Option</th><th id="d486748e29-desc">Description</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e33" class="stentry choption"><strong>Filter by</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Select how you want to determine who to create the bulk HR case                                for:</p>                            <div class="p">                                <ul class="ul" id="sn_hr_core_hr_generate_mass_cases-normal__ul_ncj_cpn_2bb"><li class="li">Upload file: Upload a file with user names or email                                        addresses.</li><li class="li">HR criteria: Use pre-defined HR criteria. Criteria based on                                        conditions defined by the <span class="ph uicontrol">HR Profile                                            [sn_hr_core_profile]</span> table. The base system                                        provides examples that can be used.</li><li class="li">User criteria: Use conditions defined by the <span class="ph uicontrol">User                                            [sys_user]</span> table. </li><li class="li">HR profile: Use conditions based on the <span class="ph uicontrol">HR                                            profile [sn_hr_core_profile]</span> table with                                        custom conditions you choose.</li><li class="li">Users: Use conditions defined by the <span class="ph uicontrol">User                                            [sys_user]</span> table with custom conditions you                                        choose.</li></ul>                            </div>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e78" class="stentry choption"><strong>Upload file</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <div class="p">Appears when <span class="ph uicontrol">Upload file</span> is selected from the                                    <span class="ph uicontrol">Filter by</span> field. Check the one you are                                    uploading:<ul class="ul" id="sn_hr_core_hr_generate_mass_cases-normal__ul_lgm_ztn_qbb"><li class="li">user_name template: Indicates that you are uploading a file                                        with user names.</li><li class="li">email template: Indicates that you are uploading a file with                                        email addresses.</li></ul></div>                            <p class="p">Click <span class="ph uicontrol">Download Template</span> to download a                                pre-formatted Excel spreadsheet.</p>                            <div class="p">                                <div class="note note"><span class="notetitle">Note:</span> The header of the first column must contain user_name or                                    email.</div>                            </div>                            <p class="p">The <span class="ph uicontrol">Upload</span> button activates after a file is                                selected.</p>                            <p class="p">After uploading the file, the number of users appears. This number                                represents the number of HR cases to be created.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e125" class="stentry choption"><strong>HR criteria</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">The base system provides pre-defined HR criteria to determine the                                    <span class="ph uicontrol">Subject person</span> of each HR case                                created.</p>                            <p class="p">Select one or more HR criteria.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e143" class="stentry choption"><strong>User criteria</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">The base system provides pre-defined User criteria to determine the                                    <span class="ph uicontrol">Subject person</span> of each HR case                                created.</p>                            <p class="p">Select a User criteria.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e161" class="stentry choption"><strong>HR profiles</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Select filter conditions on the <span class="ph uicontrol">HR profile                                    [sn_hr_core_profile]</span> table to determine the                                    <span class="ph uicontrol">Subject person</span> of each HR case                                created.</p>                            <p class="p">Select one or multiple conditions.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e183" class="stentry choption"><strong>Users</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Select filter conditions on the <span class="ph uicontrol">User                                    [sys_user]</span> table to determine the <span class="ph uicontrol">Subject                                    person</span> of each HR case created.</p>                            <p class="p">Select one or multiple conditions.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e204" class="stentry choption"><strong>All cases have same Opened for</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Check to assign the same person as the <span class="ph uicontrol">Opened                                    for</span> on each case.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e219" class="stentry choption"><strong>Opened for</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Appears when <span class="ph uicontrol">All cases have same Opened for</span> is                                checked. </p>                            <p class="p">Select the person that is the <span class="ph uicontrol">Opened for</span> on                                each case created.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e240" class="stentry choption"><strong>HR service</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Select the <span class="ph uicontrol">HR Service</span> for the bulk case.</p>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e255" class="stentry choption"><strong>Short description</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Enter a short description of the bulk case creation.</p>                            <div class="p">                                <div class="note note"><span class="notetitle">Note:</span> This field auto-fills by the HR template when the HR service                                    is selected, but you can edit it.</div>                            </div>                        </td></tr><tr class="strow chrow"><td id="d486748e273" class="stentry choption"><strong>Create a parent case (Choose this if you want to group the cases                            under a parent case)</strong></td><td class="stentry chdesc">                            <p class="p">Check to indicate that you want to create a parent case with the bulk                                cases as a child cases. </p>                            <p class="p">A parent case with the <span class="ph uicontrol">HR service</span> as                                    <span class="ph uicontrol">Bulk Parent Case</span> and the person creating                                the bulk case as the <span class="ph uicontrol">Subject person</span> is                                created.</p>                        </td></tr></tbody></table>            </div>    </div>]]></content>
